\ curry ( value xt -- xt' ): bind a value into a new anonymous word — xt'
\ pushes the value, then calls xt. The bound value is captured at curry time;
\ the curried xt travels through other words' frames intact.

\ === basic partial application ===
5 ' + curry constant add-five
10 add-five execute . cr             \ 15
3 add-five execute . cr              \ 8

clear

\ === any value kind binds: floats, arrays, xts ===
[ 1 2 3 ] 2 ' take curry execute .a cr                       \ [ 1 2 ]
' sqrt ' execute curry constant apply-sqrt
16 apply-sqrt execute . cr                                   \ 4

clear

\ === a curried quotation survives another word's locals frame ===
: mapper-word |> items quotation | items quotation map ; internal
[ 4 9 16 ] ' sqrt [> element xt | element xt execute :] curry mapper-word .a cr  \ [ 2 3 4 ]

clear

\ === capture is by value at curry time ===
variable bound-source
7 to bound-source
bound-source ' negate curry constant negate-seven
9 to bound-source
negate-seven execute . cr            \ -7 (rebinding the variable after curry changes nothing)

clear

\ === errors ===
[: 1 2 curry :] [: . cr :] try-catch          \ (top is not an xt)
[: 5 curry :] [: . cr :] try-catch            \ (needs two operands)
